 For ages, the financial services and products market in Kenya has been dominated by commercial banks and microfinance institutions. 

But, of late, unconventional lenders mostly premised on the online platforms and, as such, widely known as “digital lenders”, have emerged to plug the gap between increasing demand and declining access to quick credit. 



